<i>♪ But my jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

871
01:02:36.900 --> 01:02:40.940
<i>♪ Come all</i>
<i>ye pretty fair maids ♪</i>

872
01:02:41.420 --> 01:02:44.980
<i>♪ Whoever you may be ♪</i>

873
01:02:45.260 --> 01:02:49.180
<i>♪ Who love</i>
<i>a jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

874
01:02:49.460 --> 01:02:52.660
<i>♪ That plow</i>
<i>the raging sea ♪</i>

875
01:02:53.980 --> 01:02:58.060
<i>♪ My heart is</i>
<i>pierced by Cupid ♪</i>

876
01:02:58.140 --> 01:03:02.180
<i>♪ I disdain</i>
<i>all glittering gold ♪</i>

877
01:03:02.460 --> 01:03:06.220
<i>♪ There is nothing</i>
<i>can console me ♪</i>

878
01:03:07.060 --> 01:03:10.700
<i>♪ But my jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

879
01:03:12.060 --> 01:03:15.820
<i>♪ My heart</i>
<i>is pierced by Cupid ♪</i>

880
01:03:16.220 --> 01:03:20.100
<i>♪ I disdain</i>
<i>all glittering gold ♪</i>

881
01:03:20.220 --> 01:03:24.260
<i>♪ There is nothing</i>
<i>can console me ♪</i>

882
01:03:24.380 --> 01:03:28.740
<i>♪ But my jolly sailor bold ♪</i>

883
01:03:34.020 --> 01:03:37.420
[hissing]
[muffled scream]

884
01:03:37.500 --> 01:03:38.740
[shrieks]

885
01:03:38.860 --> 01:03:42.140
[grunts]
[men shouting]

886
01:03:47.700 --> 01:03:50.020
[shrieking]
[shouting]

887
01:03:53.020 --> 01:03:54.820
[shouting]

888
01:03:59.940 --> 01:04:01.700
[shrieking]

889
01:04:03.580 --> 01:04:07.340
[men shouting]
Out upon it! It has begun!

890
01:04:10.380 --> 01:04:11.700
[all grunting]

891
01:04:11.820 --> 01:04:15.380
[shouting]
[mermaids hissing]

892
01:04:17.260 --> 01:04:18.180
[men screaming]

893
01:04:25.700 --> 01:04:27.820
[shrieking]
[gasps]

894
01:04:28.380 --> 01:04:30.020
[screaming]

895
01:04:37.580 --> 01:04:39.300
[shrieking continues]

896
01:04:40.660 --> 01:04:43.220
[indistinct screaming]

897
01:04:44.740 --> 01:04:46.980
[gurgling]

898
01:04:49.500 --> 01:04:51.020
Light 'em up!

899
01:04:51.100 --> 01:04:55.820
Muster your courage!
Drive 'em to shore!

900
01:04:59.900 --> 01:05:02.660
[grunts]
[mermaid screams]

901
01:05:05.980 --> 01:05:09.540
Nets into the water!
Quickly!

902
01:05:09.820 --> 01:05:11.380
[shrieking continues]

903
01:05:12.540 --> 01:05:14.420
[all shouting]

904
01:05:22.740 --> 01:05:23.860
[sword vibrates]

905
01:05:28.660 --> 01:05:30.780
[mermaids shrieking]

906
01:05:47.100 --> 01:05:48.420
[net whips]

907
01:05:48.500 --> 01:05:50.140
[whipping continues]
[grunting]

908
01:05:50.220 --> 01:05:52.260
[men screaming]

909
01:05:54.500 --> 01:05:56.900
[shrieks]
[screams]

910
01:05:56.980 --> 01:05:59.180
[all shouting]

911
01:05:59.300 --> 01:06:02.180
Retreat, all, to land!
For your lives!

912
01:06:02.700 --> 01:06:04.780
[shrieks and screams continue]

913
01:06:05.700 --> 01:06:07.060
Retreat, I say!

914
01:06:07.140 --> 01:06:09.620
Cowards! Back in the water!

915
01:06:09.740 --> 01:06:13.620
There be no refuge on land!
On my word!

916
01:06:14.300 --> 01:06:15.260
[yelps]

917
01:06:17.860 --> 01:06:20.620
[shrieks of
approaching mermaids]

918
01:06:34.500 --> 01:06:35.420
[gasps]

919
01:06:35.500 --> 01:06:38.140
[hissing]
[gasps]

920
01:06:46.860 --> 01:06:48.260
Come on!

921
01:06:48.340 --> 01:06:50.820
[all clamoring]

922
01:06:59.020 --> 01:07:00.940
[shrieks]
[grunts]

923
01:07:06.780 --> 01:07:09.580
[grunts]
[screams]

924
01:07:17.380 --> 01:07:19.180
[breathes heavily]

925
01:07:33.740 --> 01:07:35.260
[grunting]

926
01:07:44.740 --> 01:07:47.620
[faint screaming, shrieking]

927
01:08:07.740 --> 01:08:09.020
[grunts]

928
01:08:14.380 --> 01:08:17.100
[muffled shrieking]

929
01:08:22.860 --> 01:08:24.660
We got one!

930
01:08:29.300 --> 01:08:31.020
I'm in love!

931
01:08:33.140 --> 01:08:34.820
Check the wounded!

932
01:08:35.180 --> 01:08:38.300
See if you can find
one mermaid still alive!

933
01:08:39.180 --> 01:08:40.500
[groans]

934
01:08:41.740 --> 01:08:44.260
[splashing nearby]

935
01:08:58.100 --> 01:08:59.260
[gasps]

936
01:09:04.580 --> 01:09:06.380
[panting]

937
01:09:13.380 --> 01:09:14.700
[hissing]

938
01:09:17.180 --> 01:09:19.620
Come, give a hand!
[hisses]

939
01:09:19.740 --> 01:09:21.620
Well done, sailor.

940
01:09:22.780 --> 01:09:24.300
Did everyone see that?

941
01:09:24.380 --> 01:09:26.540
Because I will not
be doing it again.

942
01:09:26.620 --> 01:09:31.300
Back to the ship. We head
for a protected cove. Now.

943
01:09:32.060 --> 01:09:35.540
[hissing]

944
01:09:47.900 --> 01:09:49.620
[man] Lord. Is that...?

945
01:09:49.700 --> 01:09:51.180
[Gibbs] Mermaid.

946
01:09:51.260 --> 01:09:54.780
Give up this madness now.
I cannot.

947
01:09:55.540 --> 01:09:57.180
Ever walk on the beach,

948
01:09:57.260 --> 01:09:59.220
look back and see your
footsteps in the sand?

949
01:09:59.340 --> 01:10:02.980
It's like that, except
the footsteps lie before me.

950
01:10:03.380 --> 01:10:07.420
Footstep, actually.
Whitecap Bay, sir.

951
01:10:07.500 --> 01:10:09.940
We must hasten.
[shrieking]

952
01:10:13.580 --> 01:10:16.460
[men screaming]

953
01:10:17.020 --> 01:10:20.500
We travel by foot.
Gibbs, I require a heading.

954
01:10:20.740 --> 01:10:23.780
But, sir, the men.
They be dead already.

955
01:10:23.860 --> 01:10:27.300
They don't sound dead.
Oh, is that so?

956
01:10:27.420 --> 01:10:31.180
Well, I hear nothing
but seagulls nesting.

957
01:10:31.580 --> 01:10:33.820
What is it that you hear,
Mr. Groves?

958
01:10:33.940 --> 01:10:35.980
[men continue shrieking]

959
01:10:36.580 --> 01:10:39.300
Seagulls... nesting.

960
01:10:40.180 --> 01:10:43.500
Nothing more.
Heading, Gibbs?

961
01:10:46.580 --> 01:10:50.420
[wood creaking]
[screaming continues]

962
01:10:52.020 --> 01:10:53.860
My God.

963
01:10:53.940 --> 01:10:56.020
[gun cocking]
Your head or my heading.

964
01:10:56.100 --> 01:10:58.180
I'll have me one or t'other,
I don't care which.

965
01:10:58.300 --> 01:11:00.580
[panting]

966
01:11:03.340 --> 01:11:05.660
All hands, forward!

967
01:11:21.300 --> 01:11:25.740
It's to you now, Sparrow.
Was that really necessary?

968
01:11:25.900 --> 01:11:28.380
Best you not know the exact
whereabouts of my ship.

969
01:11:28.460 --> 01:11:32.220
I be a cautious man.
So be I.

970
01:11:33.300 --> 01:11:35.100
What I want first...

971
01:11:35.220 --> 01:11:37.260
[clicking]

972
01:11:38.900 --> 01:11:40.900
...is Ponce De Leon's ship.

973
01:12:11.300 --> 01:12:13.340
[insects chittering]

974
01:12:14.340 --> 01:12:17.500
[birds squawking]

975
01:12:17.860 --> 01:12:19.820
Why is it we've got
to bring her along?

976
01:12:19.940 --> 01:12:22.900
Because tears don't keep.
We need them fresh.

977
01:12:23.220 --> 01:12:25.060
What is the ritual again?

978
01:12:26.100 --> 01:12:28.740
Water from the Fountain
and a mermaid's tear?

979
01:12:28.820 --> 01:12:30.220
And two silver chalices.

980
01:12:30.340 --> 01:12:32.500
One cup with a tear,
one without.

981
01:12:34.260 --> 01:12:36.780
So, one with a tear
and water in both?

982
01:12:36.860 --> 01:12:38.340
Quite complicated,
is it not?

983
01:12:38.420 --> 01:12:41.460
Both get water.
One gets a tear.

984
01:12:41.540 --> 01:12:44.300
The person who drinks
the water with the tear

985
01:12:44.380 --> 01:12:46.980
gets all the years
of life from the other.

986
01:12:48.220 --> 01:12:50.860
How many years? Whoa.

987
01:12:51.740 --> 01:12:54.780
All the years
that they have lived,

988
01:12:54.900 --> 01:12:58.980
and they could have lived,
if fate had been kinder.

989
01:12:59.060 --> 01:13:00.660
[hissing]

990
01:13:07.540 --> 01:13:08.820
Clergyman.

991
01:13:10.700 --> 01:13:13.860
On the off chance that this
does not go well for me,

992
01:13:13.940 --> 01:13:15.700
I would like it noted
here and now

993
01:13:15.780 --> 01:13:18.700
that I am fully prepared
to believe in whatever I must,

994
01:13:19.020 --> 01:13:20.860
so that I may be
welcomed into that place

995
01:13:20.940 --> 01:13:23.340
where all the goody-goodies
get to go. Savvy?

996
01:13:23.420 --> 01:13:27.300
We have
a word for that, Jack.
You can convert.

997
01:13:27.420 --> 01:13:29.660
I was thinking more
of an as-needed basis.

998
01:13:31.340 --> 01:13:32.980
[gasping]

999
01:13:33.900 --> 01:13:35.100
Quartermaster!

1000
01:13:35.500 --> 01:13:37.340
Aye?
She cannot breathe!

1001
01:13:37.420 --> 01:13:40.380
She has water.
She needs air!

1002
01:13:44.580 --> 01:13:46.940
Open this.
She will escape.

1003
01:13:47.020 --> 01:13:50.380
You're killing her.
I support the
missionary's position.

1004
01:13:50.500 --> 01:13:51.900
[laughs]

1005
01:13:51.980 --> 01:13:53.100
[grunts]

1006
01:13:55.180 --> 01:13:56.940
[gasps]

1007
01:13:57.060 --> 01:13:58.460
[panting]

1008
01:13:58.780 --> 01:13:59.940
See?

1009
01:14:05.140 --> 01:14:06.300
Onward.

1010
01:14:31.020 --> 01:14:34.380
Just as I thought.
Not this way!

1011
01:14:36.300 --> 01:14:37.980
This is the way,
isn't it?

1012
01:14:38.100 --> 01:14:40.780
'Course it is,
but we should go
around to the east.

1013
01:14:40.900 --> 01:14:43.020
That would take us out of
the path of the chalices.

1014
01:14:43.140 --> 01:14:45.140
Well, then
we'll circle back.
There is no time.

1015
01:14:45.220 --> 01:14:46.740
You're the one
who insisted on bringing
the bloody mermaid.

1016
01:14:46.820 --> 01:14:48.780
Well, the mutiny
didn't help.
You walk like a girl.

1017
01:14:48.940 --> 01:14:51.020
You would know.
Someone must go.

1018
01:14:51.980 --> 01:14:53.500
You mean split up?

1019
01:14:53.580 --> 01:14:56.380
You mean jump?
This I cannot wait to see.

1020
01:14:56.460 --> 01:15:00.460
Sparrow will go.
Find the ship,
retrieve the chalices.

1021
01:15:00.540 --> 01:15:02.700
Sparrow? What makes you
think he will come back?

1022
01:15:02.780 --> 01:15:06.100
Yes, what makes you think
he will come back?

1023
01:15:06.180 --> 01:15:08.580
We cannot trust him, Father.
I'll go.

1024
01:15:09.500 --> 01:15:10.580
She'll go.

1025
01:15:15.180 --> 01:15:16.900
How much farther
to the Fountain?

1026
01:15:17.020 --> 01:15:19.020
I'm running out of time.

1027
01:15:20.140 --> 01:15:22.860
About a day's march north,
following that river,

1028
01:15:22.940 --> 01:15:25.780
you'll get to
a series of pools.
Then you're close.

1029
01:15:28.780 --> 01:15:30.100
You will go.

1030
01:15:32.500 --> 01:15:34.980
I was sure
it would come to this.

1031
01:15:48.860 --> 01:15:50.740
You know that feeling
you get sometimes

1032
01:15:50.820 --> 01:15:52.900
when you're standing
in a high place?

1033
01:15:53.300 --> 01:15:55.100
Sudden urge to jump?

1034
01:15:57.060 --> 01:15:58.340
I don't have it.

1035
01:15:58.420 --> 01:16:01.660
[gun cocks]
I need those chalices.

1036
01:16:01.780 --> 01:16:04.300
Shoot. Save me
the bother of the fall.

1037
01:16:04.420 --> 01:16:06.820
You will go.
You will return...

1038
01:16:08.580 --> 01:16:10.660
...or I will kill her.

1039
01:16:13.460 --> 01:16:15.180
You won't kill
your own daughter.

1040
01:16:15.260 --> 01:16:18.060
Quartermaster,
get me six more pistols,

1041
01:16:18.140 --> 01:16:19.820
remove the shot
from all but two,

1042
01:16:19.940 --> 01:16:21.780
but do not
tell me which two.

1043
01:16:24.420 --> 01:16:27.260
You get to choose,
Mr. Sparrow.
Oh.

1044
01:16:30.100 --> 01:16:34.380
No. Mmm... No.

1045
01:16:37.420 --> 01:16:40.380
Yes.
You're sure?

1046
01:16:40.460 --> 01:16:41.860
'Course I am.

1047
01:16:46.700 --> 01:16:47.900
[gun clicks]

1048
01:16:50.460 --> 01:16:51.460
Again.

1049
01:16:52.380 --> 01:16:55.420
Please,
they're not even loaded.
[all gasp]

1050
01:16:56.700 --> 01:16:57.820
[all gasp]

1051
01:17:00.460 --> 01:17:01.500
Again.

1052
01:17:02.180 --> 01:17:04.220
If you're so keen
on killing her,

1053
01:17:04.300 --> 01:17:06.820
why don't you just
let her jump?
What?

1054
01:17:06.940 --> 01:17:09.980
Mm-mm!
If you jump and die,

1055
01:17:10.060 --> 01:17:12.620
then she will
have her chance. 

1056
01:17:13.780 --> 01:17:15.060
Again.

1057
01:17:18.540 --> 01:17:23.980
Oi... if I jump,
will I survive?

1058
01:17:26.980 --> 01:17:28.380
The doll.

1059
01:17:31.500 --> 01:17:33.980
[chanting in foreign language]

1060
01:17:37.740 --> 01:17:41.300
[Jack screaming]

1061
01:17:41.420 --> 01:17:42.620
[doll splashes in water]

1062
01:17:44.700 --> 01:17:49.700
Yes, now you will survive.
This is nonsense! I'm going!

1063
01:17:51.660 --> 01:17:55.420
[screaming]

1064
01:18:04.660 --> 01:18:06.380
[gasps]

1065
01:18:08.140 --> 01:18:11.180
Wet. Wet again.

1066
01:18:13.500 --> 01:18:16.940
[Quartermaster] We go on.
Due north to the Fountain.

1067
01:18:17.300 --> 01:18:18.940
Well played, Father.

1068
01:18:20.540 --> 01:18:22.780
You knew which guns
were loaded, right?

1069
01:18:25.460 --> 01:18:27.060
Of course, my love.

1070
01:18:37.180 --> 01:18:40.020
Be nice to have
a map about now.

1071
01:18:40.100 --> 01:18:42.300
Or a ship.
[crickets chittering]

1072
01:18:42.420 --> 01:18:46.460
Stop!
Hold very still.

1073
01:18:47.540 --> 01:18:50.940
Ye dare not let it
touch your skin.

1074
01:18:59.980 --> 01:19:03.180
What? What be wrong with
an older man having a hobby?

1075
01:19:03.260 --> 01:19:06.100
What are you
stopping for, eh?
Push on!

1076
01:19:06.180 --> 01:19:09.340
Push on!
You can sleep
when you're dead. Push on!

1077
01:19:11.020 --> 01:19:14.700
Fortune continues
to favor us.

1078
01:19:42.380 --> 01:19:44.660
The <i>Santiago.

1079
01:19:44.740 --> 01:19:47.260
Famously captained
by Ponce de Leon.

1080
01:19:48.060 --> 01:19:51.340
Oh. There's no one there.

1081
01:19:51.580 --> 01:19:52.620
Right, then.

1082
01:19:52.980 --> 01:19:54.780
[seagulls crying]

1083
01:20:03.420 --> 01:20:05.700
[glass shatters]

1084
01:20:22.220 --> 01:20:24.140
[panting]

1085
01:20:26.940 --> 01:20:28.620
We must not stop.

1086
01:20:30.700 --> 01:20:31.980
[gasps]

1087
01:20:36.660 --> 01:20:38.060
You will walk.

1088
01:20:55.340 --> 01:20:59.300
[grunts] I cannot.

1089
01:21:00.220 --> 01:21:01.580
Walk or die.

1090
01:21:07.980 --> 01:21:09.540
Put your arms around me.

1091
01:21:09.620 --> 01:21:12.860
I do not ask for help.
But you need it.

1092
01:21:30.140 --> 01:21:34.220
We're in a hurry, yes?
Do not fall behind.

1093
01:21:53.500 --> 01:21:55.540
Hold here till I say!

1094
01:22:08.300 --> 01:22:09.900
Such beauty.

1095
01:22:10.780 --> 01:22:13.420
Surely you're one of
God's own creations,

1096
01:22:13.860 --> 01:22:17.100
and not a descendant
of those dark creatures

1097
01:22:17.180 --> 01:22:18.900
who found
no refuge on the Ark.

1098
01:22:21.780 --> 01:22:23.220
Such beauty...

1099
01:22:25.180 --> 01:22:26.940
...and yet deadly.

1100
01:22:27.660 --> 01:22:29.540
Deadly? No.

1101
01:22:29.980 --> 01:22:31.500
You attacked me.

1102
01:22:32.260 --> 01:22:36.500
No. You are different.

1103
01:22:37.340 --> 01:22:38.700
Different?

1104
01:22:38.940 --> 01:22:42.020
Are you not? You protect.

1105
01:22:46.020 --> 01:22:47.220
[mutters] Did you...?

1106
01:22:49.100 --> 01:22:51.220
You pushed me down
out of the way.

1107
01:22:52.660 --> 01:22:57.260
You see the Fountain?
No, but we are close.

1108
01:22:57.820 --> 01:22:59.820
Bring the creature.
Cover its head.

1109
01:23:00.260 --> 01:23:01.820
She has a name!

1110
01:23:06.420 --> 01:23:07.860
Pray tell.

1111
01:23:14.300 --> 01:23:15.740
She is Syrena.

1112
01:23:20.900 --> 01:23:23.100
[grunting]

1113
01:23:44.140 --> 01:23:45.740
[grunts]

1114
01:23:53.060 --> 01:23:56.340
[wood creaking]
[wind whistling]

1115
01:23:56.660 --> 01:23:58.780
Ponce de Leon.

1116
01:24:01.860 --> 01:24:06.060
[Barbossa] If 40 pirates
dreamt 40 nights of treasure,

1117
01:24:06.140 --> 01:24:09.660
it would not match
the contents of this room.

1118
01:24:10.260 --> 01:24:11.340
You.

1119
01:24:13.900 --> 01:24:16.860
You.
No...

1120
01:24:16.940 --> 01:24:19.380
...you.
I was here first.

1121
01:24:19.460 --> 01:24:23.540
You, why are you here?
Blackbeard sent me.

1122
01:24:23.620 --> 01:24:26.180
Why are you?
Silver chalices

1123
01:24:26.260 --> 01:24:29.620
for my royal liege.
Oh, please.

1124
01:24:30.700 --> 01:24:33.020
Back, back! We have
to balance it out!

1125
01:24:34.380 --> 01:24:37.180
The whole ship will slide!

1126
01:24:40.780 --> 01:24:41.980
Right, then.

1127
01:24:42.620 --> 01:24:48.620
What if we each choose
an item of approximately
equal weight?

1128
01:24:51.500 --> 01:24:52.740
Put it back!

1129
01:24:54.220 --> 01:24:56.060
We touch nothing!

1130
01:25:00.500 --> 01:25:03.740
[objects rattling]

1131
01:25:04.260 --> 01:25:05.780
What about that?

1132
01:25:05.940 --> 01:25:07.380
The chalices.

1133
01:25:09.380 --> 01:25:11.540
Oi! Why do you
get to look first?

1134
01:25:11.620 --> 01:25:12.780
Fine, then.

1135
01:25:14.420 --> 01:25:18.300
[ship groaning]
[grunts]

1136
01:25:24.260 --> 01:25:25.260
[grunts]

1137
01:25:32.060 --> 01:25:33.380
[both] Together.

1138
01:25:36.260 --> 01:25:37.340
[Jack] Rocks.

1139
01:25:38.580 --> 01:25:39.860
The Spanish.

1140
01:25:40.580 --> 01:25:42.300
They're ahead of us, mate.

1141
01:25:43.180 --> 01:25:44.820
I shall have
a look at that map.

1142
01:25:45.260 --> 01:25:46.780
If it's what I fear...

1143
01:25:49.020 --> 01:25:50.820
[grunts]

1144
01:25:50.900 --> 01:25:54.220
[mutters indistinctly]
[coin tinkles]

1145
01:25:56.580 --> 01:25:58.460
I wonder why they
left this behind.

1146
01:26:02.060 --> 01:26:05.460
[whispering]
Don't touch the map.

1147
01:26:07.100 --> 01:26:08.260
Oh.

1148
01:26:10.700 --> 01:26:12.260
They know the path,

1149
01:26:12.540 --> 01:26:16.180
but I can also see where
they'll most likely make camp.

1150
01:26:29.540 --> 01:26:31.300
[Gibbs] Jack!
Shh!

1151
01:26:33.980 --> 01:26:37.300
Gibbs, I was just on me way
to break you out of jail.

1152
01:26:37.420 --> 01:26:41.380
Hmm.
You stole my map.

1153
01:26:41.700 --> 01:26:44.540
Oh!
Right. Best be started.

1154
01:26:47.660 --> 01:26:48.820
Ole.

1155
01:27:06.460 --> 01:27:08.300
[Blackbeard] Mermaids.

1156
01:27:10.700 --> 01:27:13.740
Careful, these pools run deep.

1157
01:27:13.820 --> 01:27:17.540
If she escapes, all is lost.
Quartermaster.

1158
01:27:17.660 --> 01:27:22.700
[hissing]
[Blackbeard] Look. Look!

1159
01:27:23.700 --> 01:27:27.460
Staked out to die,
to dry in the sun.

1160
01:27:27.540 --> 01:27:30.620
Only half in the water.
Not enough to live,

1161
01:27:30.740 --> 01:27:35.140
but just enough to make
the dying slow.

1162
01:27:35.900 --> 01:27:37.380
Think on it.

1163
01:27:37.500 --> 01:27:40.940
Your people, murdered,
harvested for their tears.

1164
01:27:41.340 --> 01:27:45.340
Syrena, won't you cry?

1165
01:27:46.020 --> 01:27:48.100
All die, even you.

1166
01:27:48.220 --> 01:27:51.540
Soon, I hear.
Listen...

1167
01:27:53.180 --> 01:27:55.460
[hisses]
Listen.

1168
01:27:55.540 --> 01:27:59.100
Can you not hear
your sisters scream?

1169
01:27:59.220 --> 01:28:02.300
[faint shrieks]
Do you not hear them?

1170
01:28:02.380 --> 01:28:04.980
We need but one tear.

1171
01:28:07.020 --> 01:28:09.540
[gasps]
Vile creature!

1172
01:28:09.620 --> 01:28:12.300
Chop off her fingers,
one by one!
Choke her!

1173
01:28:12.380 --> 01:28:14.780
[man] Cut out the tears
from behind the eyes!

1174
01:28:15.100 --> 01:28:16.780
Where's your voice in this?

1175
01:28:17.500 --> 01:28:19.020
Maybe she'll have
a change of heart

1176
01:28:19.100 --> 01:28:20.620
when the sun rises.

1177
01:28:20.700 --> 01:28:23.180
Oh, aye,
she will burn,

1178
01:28:23.260 --> 01:28:24.660
but I cannot
wait for the sun.

1179
01:28:24.740 --> 01:28:26.420
Perhaps we should
build a fire.

1180
01:28:26.500 --> 01:28:28.540
No.
Do not contest me, cleric.

1181
01:28:28.620 --> 01:28:31.700
You will not torture her.
We need only one tear.

1182
01:28:31.780 --> 01:28:35.180
I will tear every scale
from her body one by one
if I see fit.

1183
01:28:35.260 --> 01:28:37.140
If that displeases you,
go pray.

1184
01:28:37.220 --> 01:28:40.180
I was wrong. Not every soul
can be saved. Yours cannot.

1185
01:28:40.380 --> 01:28:43.100
Behold, gentlemen,
a man formerly of faith.

1186
01:28:43.180 --> 01:28:44.700
That vile creature,
as you call her,

1187
01:28:44.780 --> 01:28:46.100
is worth
a hundred of you.

1188
01:28:46.180 --> 01:28:47.540
Oh, you care for her?

1189
01:28:50.100 --> 01:28:52.020
You fancy her.

1190
01:28:53.660 --> 01:28:57.020
And do not deny what is
clear to my eyes.

1191
01:28:57.940 --> 01:28:59.380
Question is...

1192
01:29:02.580 --> 01:29:04.500
...does she fancy you?

1193
01:29:06.700 --> 01:29:10.780
By God, she does.
We are in luck!

1194
01:29:12.020 --> 01:29:14.860
Bring forth a tear...

1195
01:29:14.940 --> 01:29:17.660
...or witness the death
of this poor soul.

1196
01:29:17.780 --> 01:29:19.820
[grunts, gasps]
[hisses]

1197
01:29:19.940 --> 01:29:23.300
Syrena, if you could
manage a tear,

1198
01:29:23.380 --> 01:29:24.780
I would be grateful.

1199
01:29:26.180 --> 01:29:28.100
Sadness, yes,

1200
01:29:28.220 --> 01:29:33.620
but no sorrow... yet.
Not by your hand, Father!

1201
01:29:33.780 --> 01:29:36.540
Time and tide wait for none.
Quartermaster.

1202
01:29:37.380 --> 01:29:39.500
[grunt]
[pained cry]

1203
01:29:48.900 --> 01:29:51.660
Ooh, aye,
mermaids are tough.

1204
01:29:52.580 --> 01:29:53.940
The lot of them.

1205
01:29:54.340 --> 01:29:58.340
Tie her up like the others.
And get rid of this.

1206
01:29:59.020 --> 01:30:00.900
[Syrena struggling]

1207
01:30:03.420 --> 01:30:05.740
You are confident?
Yes.

1208
01:30:06.580 --> 01:30:09.540
I am a woman.
So is she.

1209
01:30:12.780 --> 01:30:14.340
[grunting]

1210
01:30:17.260 --> 01:30:20.420
[Gibbs]
What's your play, Jack?
Throwing in with Barbossa.

1211
01:30:21.420 --> 01:30:23.020
There is a girl...

1212
01:30:23.500 --> 01:30:26.780
...a female...
of the opposite sex.

1213
01:30:26.860 --> 01:30:30.700
When is there not?
Perhaps I should
say "damsel."

1214
01:30:30.780 --> 01:30:33.900
You're rescuing a damsel?
Well, there's a first.

1215
01:30:33.980 --> 01:30:37.180
Yes, but it's just that
I may have caused said damsel

1216
01:30:37.300 --> 01:30:39.020
some manner of harm
many moons ago.

1217
01:30:39.100 --> 01:30:40.620
Out with it.

1218
01:30:41.380 --> 01:30:44.740
Gibbs, this is
the woman from Seville.

1219
01:30:44.820 --> 01:30:47.020
Ah, you pretended
to love her,

1220
01:30:47.100 --> 01:30:48.620
then you left her
and broke her heart.

1221
01:30:48.700 --> 01:30:53.060
Worse. I may have had,
briefly, mind you...

1222
01:30:55.580 --> 01:30:58.100
...stirrings.
Stirrings?

1223
01:30:58.780 --> 01:31:02.540
Stirrings.
What? Like feelings,
you mean?

1224
01:31:02.740 --> 01:31:06.100
No, no, no.
Not quite all the way
to feelings. More like...

1225
01:31:10.100 --> 01:31:11.900
All right,
feelings, damn you.

1226
01:31:12.020 --> 01:31:16.220
And you left her still.
Ooh, that's low.

1227
01:31:18.060 --> 01:31:19.380
Thank you.

1228
01:31:20.460 --> 01:31:22.380
[branch snaps]
Shh!

1229
01:31:26.300 --> 01:31:27.660
Stealth over force.

1230
01:31:27.740 --> 01:31:31.100
I'll take it from here
on account of your condition.

1231
01:31:32.300 --> 01:31:34.140
You don't have
termites, do you?

1232
01:31:34.340 --> 01:31:36.780
I appreciate
your concern, Jack,

1233
01:31:36.860 --> 01:31:39.140
but I'll be keeping
you company all the same.

1234
01:31:39.380 --> 01:31:42.540
Hold here,
Lieutenant Commander.
Wait for my signal.

1235
01:31:56.740 --> 01:31:58.940
[indistinct chattering]

1236
01:32:12.620 --> 01:32:14.340
[indistinct chatter]

1237
01:32:14.420 --> 01:32:16.700
[Barbossa] There. That one.
That be the leader.

1238
01:32:16.860 --> 01:32:19.540
Make note of his tent
because that's where...

1239
01:32:20.260 --> 01:32:24.460
No, wait. By God,
that must be them
right there.

1240
01:32:27.260 --> 01:32:30.860
[sniffing]
Your sword smells funny.

1241
01:32:30.940 --> 01:32:35.700
Aye. Poison from the
innards of poisonous toads.

1242
01:32:35.860 --> 01:32:39.180
Just a scratch,
you're a dead man in minutes.

1243
01:32:39.340 --> 01:32:41.340
Would you mind pointing it
the other way?

1244
01:32:41.420 --> 01:32:42.780
I don't like toads.

1245
01:32:48.220 --> 01:32:49.500
What are you doing?

1246
01:32:49.580 --> 01:32:51.740
Planning an escape route.

1247
01:32:51.820 --> 01:32:53.420
Isn't that how you do it?

1248
01:32:54.380 --> 01:32:56.020
Yes.

1249
01:32:56.100 --> 01:32:59.340
Or sometimes I just...
improvise.

1250
01:33:26.140 --> 01:33:27.540
Now what?

1251
01:33:27.980 --> 01:33:31.020
We stroll out,
slow and steady.

1252
01:33:31.100 --> 01:33:32.820
Just like we belong.

1253
01:33:43.980 --> 01:33:46.020
[all grunting]
[swords clanging]

1254
01:34:06.620 --> 01:34:08.660
[guns cocking]

1255
01:34:14.860 --> 01:34:17.020
[groaning]

1256
01:34:26.380 --> 01:34:28.700
[animal chirping nearby]

1257
01:34:28.940 --> 01:34:30.220
[footsteps approaching]

1258
01:34:30.300 --> 01:34:33.900
[panting] I'm sorry, Syrena.

1259
01:34:34.860 --> 01:34:37.020
Philip, you're alive.

1260
01:34:37.260 --> 01:34:38.220
Yes.

1261
01:34:38.940 --> 01:34:40.460
You came for me.

1262
01:34:42.740 --> 01:34:43.980
Why?

1263
01:34:46.460 --> 01:34:48.820
You're different,
are you not?

1264
01:34:51.100 --> 01:34:54.700
Do you know not of kindness?
Compassion?

1265
01:35:00.380 --> 01:35:02.340
[grunting, yelling]

1266
01:35:12.460 --> 01:35:14.380
Tears of sorrow, never.

1267
01:35:14.460 --> 01:35:16.900
Mermaids be
too tough for that.

1268
01:35:17.020 --> 01:35:18.980
But tears of joy...

1269
01:35:20.740 --> 01:35:23.500
They say these be
the more potent anyway.

1270
01:35:23.620 --> 01:35:25.820
Syrena, on my word,
I had no part in this.

1271
01:35:27.620 --> 01:35:29.180
Let her go.
You don't need her now.

1272
01:35:29.260 --> 01:35:32.180
Let her go? No.

1273
01:35:32.260 --> 01:35:35.100
Secure her bonds.
We leave her with her own.

1274
01:35:44.700 --> 01:35:47.300
[Jack] How's that
escape route working?

1275
01:35:47.380 --> 01:35:49.500
Here's your chance
to improvise.

1276
01:35:50.100 --> 01:35:51.660
I'm attempting it.

1277
01:35:51.780 --> 01:35:54.460
I might be able to get
a hand loose.

1278
01:35:54.540 --> 01:35:56.900
Oh, you got a knife.
That's very good.

1279
01:35:57.900 --> 01:35:59.140
Better.

1280
01:36:01.140 --> 01:36:02.780
[liquid sloshing]

1281
01:36:04.820 --> 01:36:06.220
I want one of those.

1282
01:36:10.860 --> 01:36:14.580
Here's to revenge.
Sweet and clear.

1283
01:36:15.420 --> 01:36:16.900
Revenge?

1284
01:36:17.540 --> 01:36:19.220
Come, come, Hector.

1285
01:36:19.300 --> 01:36:21.220
If you wanted
the chalices,

1286
01:36:21.300 --> 01:36:23.300
you'd seen they were
missing and gone.

1287
01:36:23.900 --> 01:36:27.420
You were lying in wait,
for Blackbeard.

1288
01:36:28.180 --> 01:36:29.420
Oh?

1289
01:36:29.500 --> 01:36:32.620
King George.
Privateer. Wig.

1290
01:36:33.820 --> 01:36:36.260
Cheap theatrical facade.
I'm not buying it.

1291
01:36:36.380 --> 01:36:38.340
You weren't there that night.

1292
01:36:38.460 --> 01:36:39.820
When the <i>Pearl</i> was lost?

1293
01:36:39.940 --> 01:36:42.380
Taken, not lost.

1294
01:36:44.500 --> 01:36:46.420
We were off the coast
of Hispaniola when

1295
01:36:46.500 --> 01:36:48.900
we came under attack.
<i>[ship creaking]</i>

1296
01:36:48.980 --> 01:36:52.300
No provocation nor warning
nor offer of parley.

1297
01:36:52.620 --> 01:36:55.180
We were peppered
with cannon fire.

1298
01:36:55.260 --> 01:36:56.380
<i>[shots firing]</i>

1299
01:36:56.460 --> 01:36:59.620
And then the sea beneath
the <i>Pearl</i> began to roil.

1300
01:36:59.700 --> 01:37:01.260
<i>[sea roiling]</i>

1301
01:37:01.340 --> 01:37:03.780
The <i>Pearl</i> was pitching
and yawing violently.

1302
01:37:03.900 --> 01:37:05.500
Every plank, every rail,

1303
01:37:05.580 --> 01:37:08.620
every spar, all at once,
began to creak.

1304
01:37:08.940 --> 01:37:11.540
The rigging had come to life.
<i>[ship creaking]</i>

1305
01:37:11.620 --> 01:37:14.380
Our own ship
turned against us...

1306
01:37:14.860 --> 01:37:18.020
...tangling the crew,
wrapping around 'em
like snakes.

1307
01:37:18.100 --> 01:37:20.100
And wrapping around me leg.

1308
01:37:20.540 --> 01:37:23.300
But me arms were free
and me sword was to hand.

1309
01:37:23.420 --> 01:37:26.540
I am the master of me ship,
not Blackbeard.

1310
01:37:27.140 --> 01:37:30.620
I am the master of my fate,
not Blackbeard.

1311
01:37:31.260 --> 01:37:34.140
So I did what needed done.

1312
01:37:40.580 --> 01:37:42.620
I survived.

1313
01:37:44.140 --> 01:37:48.540
So... you're not
after the Fountain.

1314
01:37:48.660 --> 01:37:52.340
I care not for King George
or tavern yarns

1315
01:37:52.420 --> 01:37:54.580
that give hope
for a healed limb.

1316
01:37:55.900 --> 01:38:00.020
But I'd give my left arm
for a chance at Blackbeard.

1317
01:38:00.300 --> 01:38:03.060
Not your right?
I need me good arm

1318
01:38:03.140 --> 01:38:07.900
to drive my poisoned blade
through his heart.

1319
01:38:08.700 --> 01:38:11.260
I'll see you get
the chance, mate.

1320
01:38:24.740 --> 01:38:26.940
[soft grunting]

1321
01:38:34.940 --> 01:38:37.740
[indistinct chatter
in Spanish]

1322
01:38:55.540 --> 01:38:57.780
[tree creaking]
[wind whistling]

1323
01:39:17.660 --> 01:39:19.260
[creaking]

1324
01:39:29.820 --> 01:39:31.340
The prisoner's escaping.

1325
01:39:37.100 --> 01:39:38.020
[grunting]

1326
01:39:38.740 --> 01:39:41.460
He's escaping!
Fan out! Find him!

1327
01:39:41.580 --> 01:39:44.460
Go! Go!
[gunfire]

1328
01:39:44.540 --> 01:39:47.780
Hold your fire!
I want him alive!

1329
01:39:48.740 --> 01:39:51.380
[shouting in Spanish]

1330
01:39:55.340 --> 01:39:57.460
I figured
that was the signal.

1331
01:40:14.620 --> 01:40:16.900
[men yelling]

1332
01:40:23.940 --> 01:40:25.260
[men shouting]

1333
01:40:34.620 --> 01:40:36.860
[men shouting in Spanish]

1334
01:40:40.620 --> 01:40:42.340
Go! Prepare to move out!

1335
01:40:42.420 --> 01:40:43.900
The enemy is soon upon us.

1336
01:40:45.940 --> 01:40:47.580
I'm sorry about
the chalices, Jack,

1337
01:40:47.660 --> 01:40:48.940
but I've an
appointment to keep.

1338
01:40:49.020 --> 01:40:50.220
I'll not be going back.

1339
01:40:50.340 --> 01:40:51.540
No need.

1340
01:40:52.380 --> 01:40:53.540
Shall we have a drink?

1341
01:40:53.620 --> 01:40:55.140
We'll drink at the Fountain.

1342
01:41:06.180 --> 01:41:08.620
[birds chirping]

1343
01:41:11.860 --> 01:41:13.580
[gasps]

1344
01:41:14.100 --> 01:41:15.580
How is it we can never meet

1345
01:41:15.660 --> 01:41:17.660
without you pointing
something at me?

1346
01:41:18.020 --> 01:41:20.380
You brought the chalices,
Sparrow?

1347
01:41:20.500 --> 01:41:22.700
Aye. Oi!

1348
01:41:23.140 --> 01:41:26.380
[pig oinking]

1349
01:41:26.460 --> 01:41:29.180
[Angelica] I see you
brought a friend.
[Jack] I did.

1350
01:41:29.260 --> 01:41:33.100
And the one-legged man,
he is near. Aye?

1351
01:41:33.220 --> 01:41:34.180
Aye.

1352
01:41:35.460 --> 01:41:38.100
Now... Before I go
just handing them over,

1353
01:41:38.180 --> 01:41:39.500
I do have one
or two conditions.

1354
01:41:39.580 --> 01:41:41.180
Name them.
Firstly,

1355
01:41:41.300 --> 01:41:43.020
I'll be having
me compass back.

1356
01:41:43.100 --> 01:41:44.460
No, no,
that's secondly.

1357
01:41:44.540 --> 01:41:46.460
Firstly, upon your word,

1358
01:41:46.540 --> 01:41:48.660
you will bring
no harm to Angelica.

1359
01:41:48.780 --> 01:41:51.180
[Blackbeard] I'll make
no vows to the likes
of you, Sparrow.

1360
01:41:51.580 --> 01:41:54.220
But it costs me
nothing to admit

1361
01:41:54.300 --> 01:41:56.660
that she was never
in harm's way.

1362
01:41:57.180 --> 01:41:59.260
Secondly then,
priorly firstly,

1363
01:41:59.340 --> 01:42:01.260
I will be having
me compass back.

1364
01:42:01.900 --> 01:42:04.220
Please? I do deserve it.

1365
01:42:04.300 --> 01:42:05.940
Do you have any idea
how difficult it was

1366
01:42:06.020 --> 01:42:07.300
to catch that filthy pig?

1367
01:42:07.420 --> 01:42:10.300
Not the big one,
the four-legged one.

1368
01:42:13.260 --> 01:42:17.660
Thank you.
And thirdly, Mr. Beard,

1369
01:42:18.180 --> 01:42:20.500
there are times,
not very often,

1370
01:42:20.620 --> 01:42:23.740
when I do reflect
upon my heinous misdeeds.

1371
01:42:23.860 --> 01:42:28.140
Chief among them,
I note how poorly I have
treated Mr. Gibbs,

1372
01:42:28.220 --> 01:42:29.420
my loyal first mate.

1373
01:42:29.500 --> 01:42:31.380
Aye! Now you bring it up...

1374
01:42:31.460 --> 01:42:33.780
Left him to rot in jail,
I did. Didn't care.

1375
01:42:33.900 --> 01:42:38.260
Still don't. But, point being,
you must let him go free.

1376
01:42:40.140 --> 01:42:41.340
Is that it?

1377
01:42:42.220 --> 01:42:43.420
I think so.

1378
01:42:43.940 --> 01:42:46.500
Quick, or the pig runs,
and good luck getting
those chalices.

1379
01:42:46.580 --> 01:42:48.140
Jack, if it's all the same
to you, I'd be just as...

1380
01:42:48.260 --> 01:42:48.980
Done.

1381
01:42:49.100 --> 01:42:50.860
Release the swine.

1382
01:42:50.940 --> 01:42:52.180
[squealing]

1383
01:42:56.740 --> 01:42:58.100
Perhaps, if you don't mind,

1384
01:42:58.180 --> 01:43:00.260
I could tag along
with you folk for a...

1385
01:43:02.460 --> 01:43:05.020
This will lead you
to freedom, mate.

1386
01:43:11.660 --> 01:43:14.220
I could have swore it was
somewhere right around here.

1387
01:44:40.300 --> 01:44:42.420
[crackling]

1388
01:44:44.460 --> 01:44:46.260
We must not stop.

1389
01:45:03.260 --> 01:45:05.980
Aha! Dead end.

1390
01:45:06.420 --> 01:45:08.620
Dead. End.

1391
01:45:09.140 --> 01:45:10.700
[Jack] Dead end.

1392
01:45:11.620 --> 01:45:13.020
Jack, I'm starting to think

1393
01:45:13.100 --> 01:45:14.700
you don't know
where you're going.

1394
01:45:15.340 --> 01:45:18.300
It is not the destination
so much as the journey,
they say.

1395
01:45:19.620 --> 01:45:21.340
Chalices, if you please.

1396
01:45:33.140 --> 01:45:34.460
Stand back.

1397
01:45:44.180 --> 01:45:48.540
[chalices clinking,
tone echoing]

1398
01:45:53.700 --> 01:45:56.220
[chalices clinking,
tone echoing]

1399
01:45:56.300 --> 01:45:58.580
[clears throat]
Jack...

1400
01:45:58.700 --> 01:46:00.580
...have you ever, in fact...

1401
01:46:00.700 --> 01:46:06.300
...seen with
your own eyes...
the Fountain of Youth?

1402
01:46:06.420 --> 01:46:08.940
I'm sorry, could you repeat
the question, please?

1403
01:46:09.020 --> 01:46:10.180
Quartermaster.

1404
01:46:10.300 --> 01:46:12.020
[gun cocking]
No, no!

1405
01:46:12.140 --> 01:46:14.060
[firing, bullet ricocheting]

1406
01:46:14.180 --> 01:46:17.900
[gun cocking]
Wait, wait! Wait.

1407
01:46:21.220 --> 01:46:24.700
<i>"Aqua... de Vida."</i>

1408
01:46:25.220 --> 01:46:28.380
[low rumbling]

1409
01:47:04.940 --> 01:47:06.260
Master Scrum...

1410
01:47:07.420 --> 01:47:08.900
...do you mind?

1411
01:47:08.980 --> 01:47:10.260
Squire?

1412
01:47:26.660 --> 01:47:28.460
[grunting]

1413
01:47:43.660 --> 01:47:46.340
[birds chirping]

1414
01:48:09.260 --> 01:48:11.260
So beautiful.

1415
01:48:50.660 --> 01:48:54.220
Sparrow, I'll be the first
to taste those waters.

1416
01:48:57.580 --> 01:48:59.020
Father.

1417
01:49:02.380 --> 01:49:04.140
The one-legged man.

1418
01:49:07.260 --> 01:49:08.660
You brought him here.

1419
01:49:09.380 --> 01:49:11.060
Would I do that?

1420
01:49:11.140 --> 01:49:13.460
[Barbossa] Edward Teach!

1421
01:49:13.900 --> 01:49:16.780
For crimes committed
on the high seas,

1422
01:49:16.860 --> 01:49:20.780
by the authority granted me
by His Majesty the King...

1423
01:49:20.860 --> 01:49:24.260
...and with a goodly amount
of personal satisfaction...

1424
01:49:24.340 --> 01:49:27.540
...I hereby place you
in the custody of the court,

1425
01:49:27.620 --> 01:49:31.100
and declare you
to be my prisoner.

1426
01:49:31.980 --> 01:49:35.620
My trick's out, is that it?

1427
01:49:35.700 --> 01:49:40.860
Such crimes do include,
but are not limited to,
piracy, treason,

1428
01:49:40.940 --> 01:49:44.380
murder, torture of
the most heinous sort,

1429
01:49:44.460 --> 01:49:46.980
including the brutal theft
of one used,

1430
01:49:47.060 --> 01:49:49.020
twisted, hairy right leg.

1431
01:49:49.100 --> 01:49:54.180
You... dare face
this sword?

1432
01:49:54.300 --> 01:49:56.780
This far away
from your ship? Aye.

1433
01:49:56.900 --> 01:50:01.540
Aye. That be the cold breath
of fate I feel down my nape.

1434
01:50:01.620 --> 01:50:07.380
But I'll have
one last fight, by God.

1435
01:50:07.460 --> 01:50:08.620
Kill 'em all!
[men yelling]

1436
01:50:08.740 --> 01:50:12.740
Whoa, whoa!
Hang on a minute.

1437
01:50:13.220 --> 01:50:16.140
I just... I just need
to understand something.

1438
01:50:16.540 --> 01:50:20.260
Right, so, you will
fight against them,

1439
01:50:20.340 --> 01:50:21.940
they will fight
against you.

1440
01:50:22.020 --> 01:50:24.540
All on account of him
wanting to kill him?

1441
01:50:25.740 --> 01:50:27.580
Where is the sense?

1442
01:50:27.900 --> 01:50:29.500
Exactly.

1443
01:50:29.620 --> 01:50:33.380
I say, let them fight
each other while we lay back,

1444
01:50:33.500 --> 01:50:37.060
watch, have a drink,
place some wagers! Eh?

1445
01:50:37.180 --> 01:50:39.500
Hmm. Aye.

1446
01:50:42.020 --> 01:50:43.580
Kill 'em!
No quarter!

1447
01:50:43.700 --> 01:50:45.860
[men shouting]
[swords clanging]

1448
01:50:45.980 --> 01:50:47.660
[gunfire]

1449
01:51:13.220 --> 01:51:15.700
[groaning]
Get off me!

1450
01:51:38.980 --> 01:51:41.900
[shouting continues]
[swords clanging]

1451
01:51:46.220 --> 01:51:48.620
[Angelica grunting]

1452
01:51:48.740 --> 01:51:50.180
Scrum, the chalices!

1453
01:51:52.020 --> 01:51:53.620
And the tear! Follow!

1454
01:51:57.140 --> 01:51:58.140
[Blackbeard] Fight!

1455
01:51:59.220 --> 01:52:01.780
Hand it over. The tear.

1456
01:52:01.860 --> 01:52:03.060
There's a good lad.

1457
01:52:03.500 --> 01:52:05.020
I'm more afraid of her
than I am of you.

1458
01:52:08.220 --> 01:52:10.460
[grunting]

1459
01:52:10.540 --> 01:52:13.100
Hand it over.
There's a good lad.

1460
01:52:16.700 --> 01:52:18.420
The chalices, if you please.

1461
01:52:18.540 --> 01:52:20.460
[chuckles] Sorry, Jack.

1462
01:52:20.540 --> 01:52:24.620
I told you, I need years.
And now, yours will do.

1463
01:52:29.260 --> 01:52:30.420
Aha!

1464
01:52:32.620 --> 01:52:33.900
Scrum!

1465
01:52:53.100 --> 01:52:55.420
[panting]

1466
01:52:55.500 --> 01:52:56.900
Syrena...

1467
01:53:00.660 --> 01:53:03.500
My God, you will
not take her.

1468
01:53:03.620 --> 01:53:07.740
If you have taken her,
you will give her back.

1469
01:53:08.180 --> 01:53:11.100
Give her back...
[panting]

1470
01:53:11.460 --> 01:53:13.900
[whispers] Give her back,
please. Please.

1471
01:53:25.900 --> 01:53:27.060
[swords clanging]

1472
01:53:27.180 --> 01:53:28.660
[both grunting]

1473
01:53:31.340 --> 01:53:33.660
[growling]
[grunting]

1474
01:53:36.060 --> 01:53:40.340
[chuckles] I expected
fate to put up more
of a fight, eh?

1475
01:53:40.460 --> 01:53:41.780
[grunting]

1476
01:53:41.900 --> 01:53:43.180
[shouting]

1477
01:53:51.020 --> 01:53:52.580
[yelling]

1478
01:53:56.900 --> 01:54:00.940
I will not have that smile
on your face as I strike
you down.

1479
01:54:02.300 --> 01:54:05.700
Take a gander, Edward Teach.

1480
01:54:35.940 --> 01:54:39.260
This land is hereby forever
claimed in the glorious name

1481
01:54:39.340 --> 01:54:41.140
of His Majesty
King George... [grunts]

1482
01:54:41.220 --> 01:54:42.540
[gunshot]

1483
01:54:48.420 --> 01:54:51.020
Someone make a note
of that man's bravery.

1484
01:54:58.460 --> 01:55:01.660
<i>Senorita,</i> the chalices,
<i>por favor.</i>

1485
01:55:18.620 --> 01:55:24.460
Only God
can grant eternal life,
not this pagan water.

1486
01:55:24.700 --> 01:55:25.820
[chalices clattering]

1487
01:55:35.500 --> 01:55:38.620
Men, destroy this
profane temple!

1488
01:55:38.700 --> 01:55:41.580
[men shouting]

1489
01:55:41.700 --> 01:55:42.940
The Fountain!

1490
01:55:57.300 --> 01:55:58.620
You are a fool.

1491
01:55:58.980 --> 01:56:01.900
You seek in this place
what only faith can provide.

1492
01:56:01.980 --> 01:56:04.540
Faith? In faith,
there is light enough to see

1493
01:56:04.660 --> 01:56:07.020
but darkness enough to blind.

1494
01:56:10.700 --> 01:56:12.900
What devilry is this?

1495
01:56:12.980 --> 01:56:15.060
[gasps]

1496
01:56:16.860 --> 01:56:18.500
For the <i>Pearl.

1497
01:56:18.620 --> 01:56:20.260
What have you done?

1498
01:56:21.100 --> 01:56:22.220
[grunting]

1499
01:56:22.940 --> 01:56:25.380
Angelica! Don't!
It's poison!

1500
01:56:26.380 --> 01:56:27.420
[gasps]

1501
01:56:29.580 --> 01:56:32.460
[Barbossa]
I'm not such the fool
to take on Blackbeard

1502
01:56:32.580 --> 01:56:35.900
without a little
venomous advantage.

1503
01:56:37.260 --> 01:56:38.300
Jack!

1504
01:56:39.340 --> 01:56:41.420
[men yelling]

1505
01:56:50.540 --> 01:56:52.700
I claim Blackbeard's
ship and crew,

1506
01:56:52.820 --> 01:56:56.420
and this sword,
payment for my missing limb!

1507
01:56:56.500 --> 01:56:57.540
[rock crumbling]

1508
01:57:10.100 --> 01:57:12.700
[man] Hang on! Pull!
[grunting]

1509
01:57:36.460 --> 01:57:38.860
[speaks Spanish]

1510
01:57:57.460 --> 01:58:00.020
Do not waste my tear.

1511
01:58:04.700 --> 01:58:05.780
[gasping]

1512
01:58:29.020 --> 01:58:31.100
Drink this.
This one has the tear.

1513
01:58:31.180 --> 01:58:33.380
You must drink the other.
No!

1514
01:58:34.340 --> 01:58:37.300
I cannot save you both.
One of you must sacrifice.

1515
01:58:38.220 --> 01:58:42.380
You take it, Father,
for your soul.

1516
01:58:43.220 --> 01:58:48.220
Captain Teach, she's dying.
You must save your daughter.

1517
01:58:50.220 --> 01:58:52.100
This one takes life?

1518
01:58:52.580 --> 01:58:54.940
This one has the tear
and gives life?

1519
01:58:55.060 --> 01:58:56.380
Aye, hurry!

1520
01:59:04.980 --> 01:59:09.300
Angelica...
Save me, my child.

1521
01:59:11.420 --> 01:59:12.300
No.

1522
01:59:16.420 --> 01:59:17.620
[gasping]

1523
01:59:21.340 --> 01:59:22.940
I love you, Father.

1524
01:59:35.940 --> 01:59:37.100
Wait a minute.

1525
01:59:39.860 --> 01:59:42.500
In fact, it might have been
the other way around.

1526
01:59:43.660 --> 01:59:47.060
This cup had the tear,
that one had the other bit.

1527
01:59:47.500 --> 01:59:48.660
[Blackbeard] Trickster!
Hmm?

1528
01:59:48.780 --> 01:59:50.500
Devil!
Father!

1529
01:59:57.420 --> 01:59:59.900
You bastard!
How could you?

1530
02:00:00.060 --> 02:00:01.700
Your father saved you.

1531
02:00:01.820 --> 02:00:04.220
Perhaps his soul
is now redeemed. Eh?

1532
02:00:04.860 --> 02:00:07.100
[rumbling]

1533
02:00:17.180 --> 02:00:19.900
[wind whistling]

1534
02:00:50.180 --> 02:00:53.420
[gasping, panting]

1535
02:01:04.940 --> 02:01:06.380
You are hurt.

1536
02:01:09.100 --> 02:01:10.940
In body only.

1537
02:01:12.940 --> 02:01:17.300
My mind is at peace...
because of you.

1538
02:01:18.140 --> 02:01:19.180
Me?

1539
02:01:19.900 --> 02:01:21.020
Yes.

1540
02:01:21.980 --> 02:01:23.580
I was lost.

1541
02:01:25.500 --> 02:01:29.060
The wind, the tides...

1542
02:01:30.260 --> 02:01:32.460
...they ought to
renew a man's faith.

1543
02:01:35.100 --> 02:01:36.740
But for me, only you.

1544
02:01:38.180 --> 02:01:41.060
Philip, I can save you.

1545
02:01:41.660 --> 02:01:44.020
You need only ask.

1546
02:01:45.940 --> 02:01:48.740
I seek but one thing.

1547
02:01:49.060 --> 02:01:50.580
What is that?

1548
02:01:51.820 --> 02:01:53.380
Forgiveness.

1549
02:01:54.140 --> 02:01:56.860
If not for me, you would
never have been captured.

1550
02:01:57.740 --> 02:01:59.100
[whispers] Ask.

1551
02:02:01.420 --> 02:02:02.940
Forgive me?

1552
02:02:28.300 --> 02:02:29.700
I hate you.

1553
02:02:29.820 --> 02:02:31.940
The bloke
who saved your life?

1554
02:02:32.020 --> 02:02:35.540
The years I possess,
stolen from my own father!

1555
02:02:35.620 --> 02:02:38.660
I only helped Blackbeard
do what any father
should have done.

1556
02:02:39.140 --> 02:02:41.860
You are cruel and ignorant.

1557
02:02:44.420 --> 02:02:45.580
[yelling]

1558
02:02:46.060 --> 02:02:48.220
One pistol, one shot.

1559
02:02:48.300 --> 02:02:49.820
[gasps]

1560
02:02:49.900 --> 02:02:51.620
To kill myself
before I starve?

1561
02:02:51.860 --> 02:02:53.380
[Jack] There's no
trusting you, love.

1562
02:02:53.460 --> 02:02:56.020
Besides, this is
a well-traveled trade route.

1563
02:02:56.100 --> 02:02:57.860
You can signal a passing ship.

1564
02:02:58.140 --> 02:03:01.260
Or you can just
bite the proverbial
bullet, as it were.

1565
02:03:01.660 --> 02:03:03.860
And how will I get free
of these bonds?

1566
02:03:03.940 --> 02:03:05.980
You broke free of your bonds
half an hour ago,

1567
02:03:06.060 --> 02:03:08.500
waiting for the precise
moment to pounce.

1568
02:03:11.780 --> 02:03:13.180
Admit it, Jack.

1569
02:03:13.300 --> 02:03:14.860
You still love me.

1570
02:03:15.580 --> 02:03:17.500
If you had a sister
and a dog,

1571
02:03:17.580 --> 02:03:19.580
I'd choose the dog.

1572
02:03:20.540 --> 02:03:23.700
Treasure! There is
a chest with jewels!

1573
02:03:23.780 --> 02:03:26.020
Jewels with the power
to rule the wind and tide!

1574
02:03:26.100 --> 02:03:27.220
You're making that up!

1575
02:03:27.300 --> 02:03:30.260
Wait... [panting]

1576
02:03:30.340 --> 02:03:33.500
I am with child. Yours.

1577
02:03:34.700 --> 02:03:36.260
I don't recall
that we ever had...

1578
02:03:36.380 --> 02:03:37.220
You were drunk!

1579
02:03:37.340 --> 02:03:39.140
I've actually
never been that drunk.

1580
02:03:39.260 --> 02:03:40.500
Wait!

1581
02:03:41.780 --> 02:03:44.340
There is something
I want to say to you.

1582
02:03:44.780 --> 02:03:48.620
Something I wanted to say
from the moment we first met.

1583
02:03:49.340 --> 02:03:50.740
Go on, then.

1584
02:03:52.860 --> 02:03:54.500
I love you.

1585
02:03:57.820 --> 02:03:59.380
As do I.

1586
02:03:59.740 --> 02:04:03.500
Always have.
Always will.

1587
02:04:07.740 --> 02:04:09.220
I gotta go.

1588
02:04:09.300 --> 02:04:10.460
Jack!

1589
02:04:12.620 --> 02:04:14.420
This is not over!

1590
02:04:15.260 --> 02:04:16.540
Jack!

1591
02:04:23.340 --> 02:04:25.220
[gunshot]
[water splashes]

1592
02:04:26.100 --> 02:04:27.340
Missed!

1593
02:04:27.740 --> 02:04:31.020
[Angelica screaming
in Spanish]

1594
02:04:42.980 --> 02:04:45.820
The <i>Revenge</i> is mine.

1595
02:04:52.460 --> 02:04:54.060
Sir...

1596
02:04:56.620 --> 02:04:58.500
We found this
below decks.

1597
02:05:06.380 --> 02:05:08.060
[sword vibrating]

1598
02:05:18.500 --> 02:05:20.060
[men yelling]

1599
02:05:24.860 --> 02:05:27.020
All hands!
Ply to windward!

1600
02:05:27.140 --> 02:05:30.060
Get cracking,
ye blooming cockroaches!

1601
02:05:30.140 --> 02:05:33.180
[cackling]
[all laughing]

1602
02:05:33.260 --> 02:05:36.060
The Crown served me well.

1603
02:05:36.140 --> 02:05:38.820
But now, by the gods
of sea and sky...

1604
02:05:38.900 --> 02:05:42.620
...make way for Tortuga!

1605
02:05:42.700 --> 02:05:44.660
[men shouting]

1606
02:05:54.620 --> 02:05:57.380
Gibbs, you filthy, besotted
shellback, you made it!

1607
02:05:57.460 --> 02:05:58.820
[Gibbs] Aye!

1608
02:05:58.900 --> 02:06:00.820
And I trust
we managed a profit

1609
02:06:00.900 --> 02:06:02.740
from our joint enterprise?

1610
02:06:02.940 --> 02:06:05.220
Feast your eyes.

1611
02:06:09.860 --> 02:06:12.780
The compass led me
straight and true.

1612
02:06:12.860 --> 02:06:15.060
What of Blackbeard's men
guarding the ship?

1613
02:06:15.140 --> 02:06:18.380
I employed the selfsame
maneuver we perfected
in New Guinea.

1614
02:06:18.460 --> 02:06:19.100
Oh.

1615
02:06:19.180 --> 02:06:22.900
Seemed a shame to leave
an entire fleet behind.

1616
02:06:23.380 --> 02:06:25.500
Shame indeed.
[chuckles]

1617
02:06:33.740 --> 02:06:36.180
[bird squawking]
[squealing]

1618
02:06:37.340 --> 02:06:38.620
I hate that monkey.

1619
02:06:38.700 --> 02:06:39.740
So, the <i>Pearl...

1620
02:06:39.820 --> 02:06:41.900
Any idea how
to get her out?

1621
02:06:41.980 --> 02:06:45.340
We shall need a crossbow,
an hourglass, three goats.

1622
02:06:45.420 --> 02:06:48.660
One of us must learn to
play the trumpet whilst the
other one goes like this...

1623
02:06:48.740 --> 02:06:50.220
I know a man with a goat.

1624
02:06:50.380 --> 02:06:52.380
Good. I can go like this.

1625
02:06:54.940 --> 02:06:56.700
[Gibbs] Jack,
I have to ask...

1626
02:06:56.780 --> 02:06:59.420
You had the chalices,
the water, the tear...

1627
02:06:59.500 --> 02:07:02.500
You could have lived
maybe forever.

1628
02:07:02.580 --> 02:07:04.380
[Jack] The Fountain
does test you, Gibbs.

1629
02:07:04.460 --> 02:07:07.140
But better to not know
which moment may be your last.

1630
02:07:07.220 --> 02:07:09.620
Every morsel
of your entire being

1631
02:07:09.700 --> 02:07:12.620
alive to the infinite
mystery of it all.

1632
02:07:12.700 --> 02:07:15.500
And who's to say
I won't live forever, eh?

1633
02:07:15.780 --> 02:07:19.340
Discoverer of the
Fountain of Youth.
[chuckling]

1634
02:07:19.460 --> 02:07:21.980
[Jack] I have
no say in it, Gibbs.

1635
02:07:22.060 --> 02:07:23.980
It's a pirate's life for me.

1636
02:07:25.020 --> 02:07:26.380
Savvy?

1637
02:15:38.780 --> 02:15:40.580
[gulls crying]

1638
02:16:04.060 --> 02:16:05.900
[thunder rumbling]

1639
02:16:09.180 --> 02:16:11.220
[thunder cracks]

